job_history.work_description: Provided quality services to elderly populations who lives and or resided within their respective homes, but were in need of various services or resources available for them within the community.
Provided crisis intervention services to women and their children, coming into shelter after leaving their abusive homes.
Handled all incoming/outgoing calls from office to different court parts, DA's offices, judge's chambers, and clients being represented either by the lawyer or the bail bond agent.

Coordinated and provided community-based services, utilizing any and all resources available within the community to assist our clients living with a substance abuse addiction, mental illness, homelessness, and criminal history.
